- - name: hypogonadotropic hypogonadism
- type: disease
- source: MONDO_grouped
- details:
  - mondo_name: hypergonadotropic hypogonadism-cataract syndrome
  - group_name_bert: hypogonadotropic hypogonadism
  - mondo_definition: This syndrome is characterized by the association of hypergonadotropic hypogonadism and cataracts with onset during adolescence. It has been described in three brothers from a consanguineous family.
  - umls_description: Syndrome with the association of hypergonadotropic hypogonadism and cataracts with onset during adolescence. It has been described in three brothers from a consanguineous family. An autosomal recessive mode of transmission appears likely.
  - orphanet_definition: This syndrome is characterized by the association of hypergonadotropic hypogonadism and cataracts with onset during adolescence. It has been described in three brothers from a consanguineous family.
  - orphanet_prevalence: <1/1000000

